This is a project for a wordpress plugin which converts img tags in old posts into picture tags.
The plugin works on the fly when displaying the site. It does not change the post content.
The current image tag looks something like this:
<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-64676" src="https://www.mamanvoyage.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_1987.jpeg" alt="desert des bardenas van" width="960" height="720" />

This image tag should be converted into a picture tag like this:
<picture>
	<source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 640px)" srcset="https://www.mamanvoyage.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_1987.jpeg.webp">
	<source media="(min-width: 640px)" srcset="https://www.mamanvoyage.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_1987.jpeg">
	<source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 480px)" srcset="https://www.mamanvoyage.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_1987-640x480.jpeg.webp">
	<source media="(min-width: 480px)" srcset="https://www.mamanvoyage.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_1987-640x480.jpeg">
	<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://www.mamanvoyage.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_1987-480x360.jpeg.webp">
	<img src="https://www.mamanvoyage.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_1987-480x360.jpeg" alt="desert des bardenas van" width="480" height="360" loading="lazy">
</picture>

It is safe to assume that:
- for each original jpeg/jpg image there exists a corresponding webp image (.jpeg.webp or .jpg.webp)
- the 640 and 480 width images follow the standard wordpress naming convention with name-640xheight.jp.webp etc.

The Picture tag should order srcsets from top to bottom:
- for media min-width 640: webp version of full size image (assume 960 width)
- for media min-width 640: jpg version of full size image (assume 960 width)
- for media min-width 480: webp version of 640 wide image
- for media min-width 480: jpg version of 640 wide image
- without min-width: webp version of 480 wide image
- img fallback: 480 wide jpg

If the image is wrapped in a centered p tag, the p tag can be completly dropped since the picture will be centered via its css class. I.e. this:
<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-64676" src="https://www.mamanvoyage.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_1987.jpeg" alt="desert des bardenas van" width="960" height="720" /></p>

becomes this:
<picture>
	<source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 640px)" srcset="https://www.mamanvoyage.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_1987.jpeg.webp">
	<source media="(min-width: 640px)" srcset="https://www.mamanvoyage.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_1987.jpeg">
	<source type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 480px)" srcset="https://www.mamanvoyage.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_1987-640x480.jpeg.webp">
	<source media="(min-width: 480px)" srcset="https://www.mamanvoyage.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_1987-640x480.jpeg">
	<source type="image/webp" srcset="https://www.mamanvoyage.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_1987-480x360.jpeg.webp">
	<img src="https://www.mamanvoyage.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_1987-480x360.jpeg" alt="desert des bardenas van" width="480" height="360" loading="lazy">
</picture>

Be proactive and inventive

### Safety and permissions

Allowed without prompt:
- read files, list files, write files, get any file (html, css, js) from http://www.mamanvoyage.com/

Note: proactively suggest installation of tools which would help with your task for installation.
